  "text": "Anti-MAG paraproteinaemic neuropathy is clinically characterized by a predominantly sensory demyelinating neuropathy [CITATION_1] . It is slowly progressive and has an overall better prognosis than other chronic immunemediated neuropathies. Sometimes an upper limb postural neuropathic tremor may occur.",
